<module>
    <h>Calum</h>
    <p><g>Calum</g>
        <en>Malcolm</en> is a masculine <a href="?xx=nouns/anthroponymic_proper_nouns">anthroponymic
            proper noun</a>.</p>

    <section id="forms">
        <h>forms</h>
        <p>The principal parts of <g>Calum</g> are – <ul>
                <li><m>Calum</m> – nominative/dative (singular)</li>
                <li><m>Chaluim</m> – genitive (singular)</li>
                <li><m>A Chaluim!</m> – vocative</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h>dependents</h>
        <section id="deps-bare">
            <h>bare</h>
            <p>Like other (proper) nouns, <g>Calum</g> can occur on its own, without any
                dependents.</p>
            <p>Some examples – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha <m>Calum</m> ag obair.</gd>
                        <tr>Malcolm is working.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 6</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>An robh an cù còmhla ri <m>Calum</m> anns an achadh an diugh?</gd>
                        <tr>Was the dog with Malcolm in the field today?</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 15 [adapted]</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section id="deps-mods">
            <h>modifiers</h>
            <p>Like other (proper) nouns, <g>Calum</g> can be (post-)modified by an (attributive) <a
                    href="?xx=adjectives/adjective">adjective</a>.</p>
            <p>Some examples – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha <m>Calum mór</m> ag obair gu trang anns an achadh an diugh.</gd>
                        <tr>Big Malcolm is working busily in the field today.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 9 [adapted]</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h>uses</h>
        <section id="uses-sbj">
            <h>subject</h>
            <p>Like other (proper) nouns, <g>Calum</g> can be used as the subject of a <a
                    href="?xx=verbs/verbs">verb</a>.</p>
            <p>Examples with the predicative verb <a href="?gd=bi"><g>bi</g></a>
                <en>be</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Bha <m>Calum</m> mór.</gd>
                        <tr>Malcolm was big.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 6 [adapted]</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Nach eil <m>Calum</m> anns an achadh?</gd>
                        <tr>Isn’t Malcolm in the field?</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 11</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Có bha ag iasgach air an loch? Bha <m>Calum</m>.</gd>
                        <tr>Who was fishing on the lake? Calum was.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
            <p>Examples with <a href="?xx=nouns/demonstrative_pronouns">demonstrative pronouns</a>
                used as copular verbs – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Seo <m>Calum</m>.</gd>
                        <tr>This is Malcolm.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 15</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
            <p><g>Calum</g> can also be used as part of a conjoined subject linked by <a
                    href="?gd=agus"><g>agus</g></a>
                <en>and</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Bha <m>Màiri agus Calum</m> ag obair.</gd>
                        <tr>Malcolm and Mary were working.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 16 [adapted]</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Nach eil <m>Calum agus Seumas</m> anns an sgoil an diugh?</gd>
                        <tr>Aren’t Malcolm and James in the school today?</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 15 [228] [adapted]</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
